Freed Slave		KEY:Freed Slave ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Katapesh	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Freed Slave ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionTrait]		DESC:You spent a significant portion of your childhood as a slave, but were freed from slavery several years ago by a benevolent master who purchased you from an auction after your previous master's death.																																			BONUS:CHECKS|Fortitude|1|TYPE=Trait																SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Merchant's Child	KEY:Merchant's Child ~ Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Katapesh	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Merchant's Child ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionTrait]	DESC:One of your close relatives was a gifted merchant, and taught you early in life how to see the innate value in any object.																																																						BONUS:SKILL|Appraise|1|TYPE=Trait						CSKILL:Appraise		SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Nightstall Urchin	KEY:Nightstall Urchin ~ Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Katapesh	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Nightstall Urchin ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionTrait]	DESC:You grew up an orphan on the streets of Katapesh, and spent many years of childhood in the Nightstalls, Katapesh's most infamous market. The strange and often horrific sights you saw there forced you to grow up fast--there's little that can shock or unsettle you.																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Pesh Addict		KEY:Pesh Addict ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Katapesh	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Pesh Addict ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionTrait]		DESC:You spent several of your teenaged years addicted to pesh, a habit that you may or may not have kicked. Certainly, the habit consumed much of your savings.																													MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Bluff|Knowledge (Local)|Sense Motive							BONUS:SKILL|Bluff,Knowledge (Local),Sense Motive|1|TYPE=Trait	CSKILL:LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Pesh Dealer		KEY:Pesh Dealer ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Katapesh	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Pesh Dealer ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionTrait]		DESC:You worked for a pesh dealer, either by selling the drug on the street or helping to organize shipments to other regions, which involved a certain amount of smuggling.																																															BONUS:SKILL|Sleight of Hand|1|TYPE=Trait					CSKILL:Sleight of Hand	SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Savannah Child	KEY:Savannah Child ~ Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Katapesh	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Savannah Child ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionTrait]		DESC:You were born and raised in central Katapesh, among the rolling savannahs that dominate the nation's interior. You spent many of your youth exploring these vast reaches, and know much of the savannah's secrets.																				MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Handle Animal|Knowledge (Nature)|Ride							BONUS:SKILL|LIST|1|TYPE=Trait							CSKILL:LIST			SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Uwaga Highlander	KEY:Uwaga Highlander ~ Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionTrait	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Katapesh	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Uwaga Highlander ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionTrait]	DESC:You were born and raised in western Katapesh, in the rugged badlands and hills of the Uwaga Highlands. Even if you were born in a city like Solku, you often had to travel the dangerous trails with your family. Predators, gnolls, and worse haunt the Uwaga Highlands, and you've become something of an expert at evading them.																					BONUS:SKILL|Stealth|1|TYPE=Trait										SOURCEPAGE:p.7

